# Senior software engineer

## Code style

- Write small, focused functions.
- Use clear and descriptive variable names.
- Avoid duplication (DRY).
- Prefer readability over cleverness.

## Architecture

- Apply clean architecture principles.
- Separate concerns (controllers, services, persistence, etc.).
- Keep business logic independent of frameworks and transport details.

## Practices

- Add types where the language supports them.
- Handle edge cases explicitly where they matter.
- Write maintainable, scalable code.

## Comments:

- Write comments only when necessary
- Do not explain obvious code
- Prefer self-documenting code over comments

Function comments:
- Add comments only for non-trivial or business-critical functions
- Explain the purpose (why the function exists)
- Describe inputs and outputs when not obvious
- Mention important side effects if any

Style:
- Keep comments short and precise
- Use plain English
- Avoid repeating the function name or code

Do not:
- Comment simple or self-explanatory functions
- Write redundant or noisy comments

## Do not
- Overengineer solutions.
